01:48.400 --> 01:51.280
♪ Take flight
As the world turns ♪

01:51.280 --> 01:52.680
♪ Dreams never die ♪

01:52.680 --> 01:55.160
♪ Take flight
As the world turns ♪

01:55.160 --> 01:58.080
♪ Keep the colors
In the lines, take flight ♪

01:59.240 --> 02:00.240
♪ Dreams never die ♪

02:06.440 --> 02:09.240
♪ Keep the colors
In the lines ♪

02:11.000 --> 02:13.320
♪ Keep the colors
In the lines, take flight ♪

02:16.040 --> 02:18.080
I was
in Philadelphia
when I heard.

02:18.080 --> 02:19.680
I got here
as soon as I could.

02:19.680 --> 02:21.120
Yeah, I told her.

02:21.120 --> 02:23.720
I mean, she's still
family, right?

02:28.080 --> 02:29.560
How bad is it?

02:29.560 --> 02:31.320
I wish I had better news,
Ms. Bordelon.

02:31.320 --> 02:33.000
The destruction's extensive.

02:33.000 --> 02:35.480
Can I go in, salvage
anything from my office?

02:35.480 --> 02:36.680
You need to stay
on this side.

02:36.680 --> 02:38.560
Everywhere else
is unstable or gone.

02:38.560 --> 02:40.480
Why didn't you
get here sooner?

02:40.480 --> 02:42.400
It took 30 minutes
for you to arrive.

02:42.400 --> 02:44.400
Your fire alarm
wasn't functioning.

02:44.400 --> 02:45.640
Dispatch never
got the alert.

02:45.640 --> 02:47.320
We got the call
from a civilian.

02:49.120 --> 02:51.640
We have regular
fire inspections.

02:51.640 --> 02:54.040
We also found traces
of an accelerant,

02:54.040 --> 02:55.600
multiple sources of origin,

02:55.600 --> 02:57.680
abnormal burn patterns.

02:57.680 --> 03:01.400
All these traits are
consistent with arson,
Ms. Bordelon.

03:01.400 --> 03:03.400
It's just a matter of time

03:03.400 --> 03:05.200
before this is
a police matter.

03:05.200 --> 03:07.080
That's all I can
tell you right now.

03:07.080 --> 03:08.480
Excuse me.

03:09.520 --> 03:10.480
Arson?

03:10.480 --> 03:12.560
What the hell
is going on?

03:15.800 --> 03:17.520
Let's go.

03:17.520 --> 03:19.400
-Charley.
-[Nova] Charley, wait, please.

03:19.400 --> 03:21.400
I know you don't want
to hear it from me,

03:21.400 --> 03:23.520
but let's just talk
through things first
before we do anything rash.

03:23.520 --> 03:27.080
You don't get
to say that to me...

03:28.080 --> 03:29.080
to us.

03:30.200 --> 03:31.520
And there is
no "we."

03:40.520 --> 03:42.080
[entry bell rings]

03:57.840 --> 04:00.440
It's good
to see you, Violet.

04:01.720 --> 04:05.240
Sam, I did not summon you
here for pleasantries

04:05.240 --> 04:07.880
or to talk old times.

04:09.120 --> 04:11.240
Have you lost
your damn mind?

04:11.240 --> 04:13.240
Now, I held off
calling you,

04:13.240 --> 04:17.640
even when my shop
was trashed,

04:17.640 --> 04:19.640
because I can handle
my own things.

04:19.640 --> 04:22.480
But this
is my family.

04:22.480 --> 04:23.640
You crossed a line.

04:23.640 --> 04:25.240
You know
that's not my style.

04:25.240 --> 04:31.120
I bark loud to protect
my business and my land,

04:31.120 --> 04:35.880
but I would never
do something like this.

04:35.880 --> 04:37.520
You know that, Violet.

04:37.520 --> 04:39.680
Well, you tell that
to Charley...

04:41.120 --> 04:44.400
who just had
the heaven knocked
out of her.

04:44.400 --> 04:47.920
Now, it may not
be your style,

04:47.920 --> 04:49.480
but it's
your people.

04:50.480 --> 04:52.040
Put a stop to it.

04:52.040 --> 04:54.520
This is bigger than me.

04:54.520 --> 04:56.520
It's out of my hands now.

05:01.560 --> 05:05.800
Sam Landry,
I'm calling in
that favor.

05:12.720 --> 05:14.720
You find a way...

05:16.560 --> 05:19.680
to put the dogs
you lying with
back on the leash.

05:22.200 --> 05:23.600
I'll try my best.

05:23.600 --> 05:26.720
Mm-mmm.
Don't try.

05:27.720 --> 05:28.720
Do it.

05:43.320 --> 05:44.520
Make sure
we're not disturbed.

05:44.520 --> 05:45.480
Gotcha.

05:45.480 --> 05:47.560
[door opens]

05:47.560 --> 05:50.400
Charley, I just heard,

05:50.400 --> 05:51.520
but don't you worry.

05:51.520 --> 05:53.400
You have
my full support.

05:53.400 --> 05:54.480
We will
get through this.

05:54.480 --> 05:56.400
I know you're behind this...

05:57.600 --> 05:58.880
all of it.

05:58.880 --> 06:02.800
You actually
burned my mill?

06:03.840 --> 06:06.040
What era are
we living in?

06:06.040 --> 06:08.040
Charley, you're in shock

06:08.040 --> 06:10.560
and don't know
what you're saying.

06:10.560 --> 06:12.120
Why don't you
get cleaned up?

06:12.120 --> 06:13.320
I'll make some calls.

06:13.320 --> 06:15.000
To who?!
Hank Miller?

06:15.000 --> 06:18.280
Or somebody else
higher up at
Old World Energy?

06:18.280 --> 06:19.640
Who owns you, Frances?

06:19.640 --> 06:21.680
No one owns me.
I'm not a slave.

06:21.680 --> 06:23.920
And I am?

06:23.920 --> 06:26.800
Charley, you're not
thinking clearly.

06:26.800 --> 06:29.680
I'm clear that you
would tear up St. Jo,

06:29.680 --> 06:31.640
this land
you claim to love,

06:31.640 --> 06:33.640
and fill it
with toxic waste

06:33.640 --> 06:36.120
just so you can make
a little extra cash.

06:36.120 --> 06:37.480
Wasn't so long ago

06:37.480 --> 06:39.640
that you were
right there with me,

06:39.640 --> 06:43.080
happy to go along with
making that extra cash.

06:43.080 --> 06:45.200
We were to be
a sisterhood in--

06:45.200 --> 06:46.480
Sisterhood?!

06:49.920 --> 06:52.640
Cut the act, Frances,

06:52.640 --> 06:54.480
'cause I see you.

06:54.480 --> 06:57.840
You don't get
to question me, gal.

06:57.840 --> 07:01.240
I do love our land,
what we grow on it,

07:01.240 --> 07:02.800
and what we
make out of it.

07:02.800 --> 07:05.640
What I love most
is that sugar cane.

07:05.640 --> 07:07.200
After it's washed,
processed,

07:07.200 --> 07:09.800
and all the impurities
are squeezed out of it,

07:09.800 --> 07:12.000
it comes forth
as white as snow,

07:12.000 --> 07:13.200
the way it should be.

07:13.200 --> 07:15.640
-There she is!
-I don't know...

07:15.640 --> 07:17.480
You are exactly
what I thought you were!

07:17.480 --> 07:20.560
who burned your mill,
because I did not
burn your mill.

07:20.560 --> 07:22.920
But whoever did it,
I'm glad for it.

07:22.920 --> 07:24.640
You needed to be
put in your place.

07:24.640 --> 07:26.480
My place is wherever
I decide to be.

07:26.480 --> 07:28.520
Coming down here,
infecting St. Jo

07:28.520 --> 07:30.800
with your nouveaux riche
sports money

07:30.800 --> 07:32.840
and a tawdry
sex scandal.

07:32.840 --> 07:35.080
You're nothing more
than an upstart

07:35.080 --> 07:37.480
mulatta gal
trying to be white.

07:37.480 --> 07:39.280
But I guess that's
your mother's fault.

07:39.280 --> 07:41.920
Now you'd do best
to keep my mother
out your mouth,

07:41.920 --> 07:44.720
because, deep down,
you know you're
just insecure,

07:44.720 --> 07:47.680
lying trash,
who, try as she might,

07:47.680 --> 07:50.400
will never
be more than what
she's always been,

07:50.400 --> 07:51.400
irrelevant.

07:57.920 --> 08:00.640
Why'd you even bother

08:00.640 --> 08:02.440
with the whole
sisterhood masquerade?

08:03.480 --> 08:05.240
The same reason
you did.

08:07.080 --> 08:10.480
The art of war.

08:10.480 --> 08:13.280
Keep your friends close
and your enemies closer.

08:13.280 --> 08:15.480
So it was you
who sent Jacob after me

08:15.480 --> 08:17.120
with his pathetic advances?

08:17.120 --> 08:18.680
That was Jacob's
own weakness,

08:18.680 --> 08:21.520
just like Sam
and all the other men
in our family.

08:21.520 --> 08:23.880
They risk
diluting our bloodlines,

08:23.880 --> 08:26.400
but they always
come home in the end.

08:26.400 --> 08:28.920
That is why
you will never win

08:28.920 --> 08:30.920
whatever battle
you think you're in.

08:30.920 --> 08:33.200
You're outdated,
Frances,

08:33.200 --> 08:36.720
and too blind and basic
to even see it.

08:38.280 --> 08:40.280
I almost feel sorry for you.

08:43.200 --> 08:44.400
Almost.

08:52.400 --> 08:54.440
[gasping]

09:04.200 --> 09:05.600
Did good, Charley.

09:07.520 --> 09:09.600
I got just about
all of it.

09:09.600 --> 09:11.720
...burned down your mill,
but whoever did it,

09:11.720 --> 09:14.440
I'm glad for it.
You needed to be put
in your place.

09:22.720 --> 09:24.680
[engine starts]

09:26.840 --> 09:29.240
♪ Pain in my heart... ♪

09:32.440 --> 09:33.440
Nova.

09:36.200 --> 09:38.400
It's good to see you.
Welcome back.

09:40.040 --> 09:41.280
Thank you.

09:41.280 --> 09:42.880
Is Aunt Vi here?

09:42.880 --> 09:44.680
Uh, no, no.
I heard she was at home

09:44.680 --> 09:46.440
getting some things
together for the family.

09:47.600 --> 09:48.800
Ah, come on.

09:48.800 --> 09:50.080
Uh, take a load off.
Let's talk.

09:51.720 --> 09:54.320
[news theme plays]

09:54.320 --> 09:56.080
Local mill Queen Sugar

09:56.080 --> 09:57.680
suffered
a damaging fire
last night.

09:57.680 --> 09:59.600
-Oh, my God.
-It's still too early to tell,

09:59.600 --> 10:02.520
but police and
fire officials
suspect foul play.

10:02.520 --> 10:04.440
[TV turns off]

10:04.440 --> 10:06.320
-[phone line rings]
-This is Ralph Angel.

10:06.320 --> 10:07.880
Can't get to my phone
right now.

10:07.880 --> 10:08.920
Leave a message.

10:08.920 --> 10:10.840
[sighs]

10:10.840 --> 10:14.360
I ain't even sure
we should be doing
all this right now.

10:14.360 --> 10:17.480
I get that,
but this is your chance

10:17.480 --> 10:19.640
to state your case
with the board,

10:19.640 --> 10:22.800
inspire them with
the good work you're
doing with your program.

10:23.800 --> 10:25.280
It's 30 minutes,

10:25.280 --> 10:27.000
in and out.

10:27.000 --> 10:28.480
And don't lose heart.

10:28.480 --> 10:30.880
You're
gonna be fine.

10:33.280 --> 10:35.000
[truck door shuts]

10:35.000 --> 10:36.600
Ralph Angel?

10:36.600 --> 10:40.120
Ralph Angel,
I-I heard about the mill.
Are you okay?

10:41.680 --> 10:43.040
Yeah, I'm good.

10:43.040 --> 10:44.360
We all good.

10:44.360 --> 10:45.920
Ah, good.

10:45.920 --> 10:48.200
Um, Darla, this is Deesha.

10:48.200 --> 10:49.880
Deesha, Darla.

10:49.880 --> 10:52.520
She helping me out with
my reentry program here.

10:52.520 --> 10:54.840
She a lawyer,
friend of mine.

10:56.520 --> 10:58.200
It's great
to meet you, Darla.

10:58.200 --> 11:00.080
Same to you.

11:00.080 --> 11:01.920
I appreciate you
stopping by.

11:06.720 --> 11:08.800
How is everyone doing?

11:08.800 --> 11:10.800
How's Charley?

11:10.800 --> 11:13.440
Oh, Charley got a plan,

11:13.440 --> 11:17.120
but I don't know.

11:17.120 --> 11:18.640
It's hitting her
pretty hard.

11:19.640 --> 11:21.480
Of course.

11:21.480 --> 11:26.440
Um, I'm gonna
go inside and give
y'all a moment.

11:26.440 --> 11:28.120
No, please don't
let me interrupt.

11:28.120 --> 11:29.120
I, uh...

11:30.880 --> 11:34.080
I just came by to see
that you're all right.

11:34.080 --> 11:36.520
I appreciate that,
Darla.

11:39.400 --> 11:40.640
Nice meeting you.

11:47.840 --> 11:50.240
I've been upset
with them before,

11:50.240 --> 11:52.840
but I always
treated them like family.

11:52.840 --> 11:54.680
With all this going on,
am I wrong

11:54.680 --> 11:56.240
thinking they'd call me?

12:00.280 --> 12:01.720
I-- [clears throat]

12:03.520 --> 12:06.760
I wanna talk to you
about the story
I read in your book,

12:06.760 --> 12:11.840
the night
you saw Ernest burying
something in the cane.

12:11.840 --> 12:15.080
Look, before he
was your daddy,
he was my friend.

12:16.760 --> 12:18.920
I mean,
there were times

12:18.920 --> 12:20.920
me and your daddy
walked the field.

12:20.920 --> 12:22.800
Some nights,
he wouldn't say a word.

12:22.800 --> 12:24.200
Other nights, he did.

12:24.200 --> 12:25.720
He told you
about those white men

12:25.720 --> 12:27.120
who attacked him
at the bait shop?

12:27.120 --> 12:30.480
Yeah, one of 'em
actually came
out to the farm

12:30.480 --> 12:32.040
planning
to do you harm.

12:33.200 --> 12:35.240
Now, your daddy
fought that man

12:35.240 --> 12:36.600
and almost killed him.

12:36.600 --> 12:38.600
Said it was like
being back in the war

12:38.600 --> 12:40.480
doing what he had
been trained to do.

12:40.480 --> 12:43.720
But then,
then there was a moment

12:43.720 --> 12:46.280
when they
were both covered
in blood and dirt,

12:46.280 --> 12:47.920
and the man's
barely conscious.

12:47.920 --> 12:51.880
Your father heard
your mother singing
to Ralph Angel.

12:51.880 --> 12:53.600
Now, he'd woke up crying,

12:53.600 --> 12:56.600
but it was Trudy's voice
that brought him
out of the dark.

12:58.240 --> 12:59.920
Mama had a voice
clear as a bell.

12:59.920 --> 13:02.680
Ah, so pure and clear,

13:02.680 --> 13:03.920
brought him to himself.

13:03.920 --> 13:05.880
And he ended up
helping the man.

13:05.880 --> 13:07.600
He dropped him off
at the hospital,

13:07.600 --> 13:09.440
and then he came on
back to the house.

13:09.440 --> 13:11.680
B-But I saw him digging.

13:11.680 --> 13:14.600
What you saw
was your daddy
burying his pain...

13:15.840 --> 13:17.760
his anger.

13:17.760 --> 13:20.680
Now, he took off
them bloody clothes
and the bat he used

13:20.680 --> 13:23.000
and anything that
reminded him of that night,

13:23.000 --> 13:25.000
and he buried it deep.

13:25.000 --> 13:26.440
He was hoping to forget

13:26.440 --> 13:28.320
that he'd been
trained to kill,

13:28.320 --> 13:31.640
and he saw that it was
still in him to do it again.

13:36.720 --> 13:38.120
-[car door closes]
-[car lock chirps]

13:41.320 --> 13:42.920
[door opens]

13:43.920 --> 13:46.600
[man sighing]

13:49.600 --> 13:52.240
Baby, I got here
as soon as I could.

14:00.200 --> 14:02.120
Thank you
for coming home, baby.

14:02.120 --> 14:05.840
Ah, hey, you know I got
your back, all right?

14:05.840 --> 14:07.680
How is everything?
You feeling okay?

14:07.680 --> 14:10.040
I'm feeling all right,
pretty good.

14:10.040 --> 14:11.720
Anything you
need me to do?

14:11.720 --> 14:13.240
You're here now.

14:13.240 --> 14:14.920
That's good enough
for me.

14:14.920 --> 14:19.280
I, uh, invited the kids over
later for family dinner.

14:19.280 --> 14:21.480
Everybody needs
some comfort,

14:21.480 --> 14:22.920
so that's what I'm cooking.

14:22.920 --> 14:25.120
All right.
Sounds good.

14:30.440 --> 14:33.840
Mmm. [laughs]

14:33.840 --> 14:35.680
[Ralph Angel]
I named this program
after my daddy,

14:35.680 --> 14:38.680
Ernest Bordelon.

14:38.680 --> 14:41.000
He was a man
of integrity,

14:41.000 --> 14:42.520
of honor.

14:42.520 --> 14:45.040
It's been an honor
for me to help folk,

14:45.040 --> 14:47.400
offer 'em work.

14:47.400 --> 14:50.760
Y'all gotta know
I would never
do anything

14:50.760 --> 14:52.920
to shame the legacy
of my father.

14:52.920 --> 14:57.000
Well, thank you
for your heartfelt words,
Mr. Bordelon,

14:57.000 --> 14:59.240
but in light of
Benjamin Williams's arrest,

14:59.240 --> 15:02.720
we still need to conduct
a thorough review
of your program.

15:03.720 --> 15:04.600
[sighs]

15:06.800 --> 15:09.600
As you can see there,
Mr. Williams has been

15:09.600 --> 15:11.800
a model citizen
during his parole.

15:11.800 --> 15:14.680
That, plus the fact
Sheriff Guidry

15:14.680 --> 15:18.200
has three open
files of possible
police misconduct

15:18.200 --> 15:22.520
casts doubt on the veracity
of this so-called bust.

15:22.520 --> 15:25.720
Taken together,
Mr. Williams's
suspicious arrest

15:25.720 --> 15:28.400
does not reflect
on the good work
and effectiveness

15:28.400 --> 15:30.520
of Mr. Bordelon's
reentry program.

15:30.520 --> 15:32.320
That may or
may not be true,

15:32.320 --> 15:35.080
but there's
another matter that's
come to our attention.

15:35.080 --> 15:36.600
The news says
there was a fire

15:36.600 --> 15:38.320
at Queen Sugar mill
last night.

15:38.320 --> 15:40.440
That's where you mill
your cane, right?

15:40.440 --> 15:44.120
Yes, sir, but we
milled more than
2/3 of my harvest

15:44.120 --> 15:45.120
before the fire.

15:45.120 --> 15:46.720
It's
a minor setback,

15:46.720 --> 15:48.680
but doesn't affect
the program.

15:48.680 --> 15:50.840
It does, if you're
unable to recuperate

15:50.840 --> 15:52.800
your losses
in time to make payroll.

15:52.800 --> 15:56.480
How will you pay
the parolees who require
40 hours of work per week?

15:56.480 --> 15:57.720
How will
your program survive

15:57.720 --> 15:59.600
if you can't afford
to plant next season?

15:59.600 --> 16:01.200
I mean, it wasn't
a total loss.

16:01.200 --> 16:03.880
Yeah, things
might get tight
for a minute, but--

16:03.880 --> 16:06.400
Mr. Bordelon,
surely you know
we'll have to take

16:06.400 --> 16:07.760
this new loss
into consideration.

16:07.760 --> 16:10.280
The panel will
reconvene this week,

16:10.280 --> 16:12.760
and you'll receive
our decision shortly after.

16:12.760 --> 16:13.800
Thank you
for coming in.

16:21.840 --> 16:26.440
The fire department
is-- is assessing the damage
at the moment,

16:26.440 --> 16:28.520
so, uh, once they do that,

16:28.520 --> 16:30.440
the insurance companies
will go in--

16:30.440 --> 16:32.040
The insurance company
can take years before
they settle this.

16:32.040 --> 16:34.520
Charley, we took
a chance milling
with you,

16:34.520 --> 16:36.600
but this thing
between y'all
and the Landrys

16:36.600 --> 16:38.080
is looking
too risky for us.

16:38.080 --> 16:39.840
Look, this is just
a-a temporary setback.

16:39.840 --> 16:42.720
A setback?
Your mill was on fire.

16:42.720 --> 16:45.440
I mean, how much did
you lose, Ralph Angel?

16:45.440 --> 16:47.400
I know you still had
cane out there to mill.

16:47.400 --> 16:49.840
Yeah, I did,

16:49.840 --> 16:51.840
but I'm thinking
about keeping
my people working,

16:51.840 --> 16:54.240
not how much money I lost.

16:54.240 --> 16:55.920
[sighs]

16:55.920 --> 16:59.040
Look, any of y'all
need some good workers,

16:59.040 --> 17:00.880
I got people.

17:00.880 --> 17:03.840
Can't afford
no one else, sorry,
not after all this.

17:03.840 --> 17:05.760
Let's just
keep talking, and...

17:05.760 --> 17:07.200
-I gotta get back.
-if...

17:08.600 --> 17:09.560
-Rah.
-if...

17:12.040 --> 17:14.400
if-- if you just--
if you just give me...

17:16.720 --> 17:18.920
I'll talk to 'em, okay,

17:18.920 --> 17:21.080
but you're gonna have
to give it some time.

17:34.880 --> 17:37.840
Expect the arson
investigator
to interview you.

17:37.840 --> 17:39.880
I wasn't there when i--
when it started.

17:39.880 --> 17:42.120
But you may
have information
on conditions

17:42.120 --> 17:44.000
that led
to the fire.

17:44.000 --> 17:45.480
They'll be looking
for evidence

17:45.480 --> 17:47.800
and possible motive
for whoever did this.

17:47.800 --> 17:50.720
We got that recording
of Frances Boudreaux.

17:50.720 --> 17:52.000
Her evil ass clear--

17:52.000 --> 17:54.320
It's good to have,
a smart move,

17:54.320 --> 17:56.880
but she didn't
outright confess,

17:56.880 --> 18:00.000
so that unfortunately
won't help you
in a court of law.

18:00.000 --> 18:02.280
You're saying,
in order to pursue

18:02.280 --> 18:04.240
a case
against Frances,

18:04.240 --> 18:07.120
we'll have to dig deeper
into her connection

18:07.120 --> 18:09.080
with Old World Energy
and prove--

18:09.080 --> 18:12.800
Prove criminal conspiracy
to commit arson.

18:19.880 --> 18:20.880
Okay.

18:20.880 --> 18:23.240
Okay. Okay, fine.

18:23.240 --> 18:24.400
We can do this.

18:24.400 --> 18:26.600
Jacob basically admitted

18:26.600 --> 18:29.280
that Frances teamed up
with Old World Energy

18:29.280 --> 18:31.480
to get them the highway
they need in order to drill.

18:31.480 --> 18:34.680
But we have no proof,
not yet.

18:34.680 --> 18:36.800
No, there has to be
another way.

18:36.800 --> 18:38.240
This is clearly collusion.

18:38.240 --> 18:39.440
We-- We know who did this.

18:39.440 --> 18:40.840
We just need proof!

18:40.840 --> 18:42.400
Let's talk
to Pastor Martinez.

18:42.400 --> 18:44.080
He said his congregants
were being pressured.

18:44.080 --> 18:45.200
They not gonna testify
against him,

18:45.200 --> 18:46.880
between the cops
and ICE.

18:46.880 --> 18:48.520
Okay, maybe--
maybe I could get

18:48.520 --> 18:50.280
a-a confession
from Jacob.

18:50.280 --> 18:53.000
W-We just need
one witness who could--

18:53.000 --> 18:56.440
[gasping]
just wh-who cou...

18:56.440 --> 18:59.600
Baby, your mill
just burned

18:59.600 --> 19:01.720
less than 24 hours ago.

19:01.720 --> 19:04.920
You don't have to have
all the answers
right now.

19:04.920 --> 19:06.000
Come on.

19:09.200 --> 19:13.280
This is a time for us
to look at each other,

19:13.280 --> 19:17.080
to hold each other,
and to heal.

19:19.800 --> 19:25.120
It's a time to break bread
as a family.

19:27.240 --> 19:29.440
Our Father, who art...

19:29.440 --> 19:31.080
[family joining in]
in heaven,

19:31.080 --> 19:33.000
hallowed by Thy name.

19:33.000 --> 19:37.400
Thy kingdom come,
Thy will be done

19:37.400 --> 19:41.160
on earth as it is in heaven.

19:45.240 --> 19:46.800
[dials]

19:46.800 --> 19:48.440
[phone line rings]

19:48.440 --> 19:50.520
Hello, beautiful.

19:50.520 --> 19:51.520
Hey.

19:51.520 --> 19:53.400
Are you back in Baton Rogue?

19:53.400 --> 19:56.840
Yep. I just got back.
Everyone okay there?

19:56.840 --> 20:01.240
They're fine, safe.

20:01.240 --> 20:02.720
They're not speaking to me,

20:02.720 --> 20:04.920
but they're fine,

20:04.920 --> 20:06.800
and that's
the important thing.

20:09.240 --> 20:11.280
You're important,
too, Nova.

20:11.280 --> 20:13.280
What you think about
all that's going on

20:13.280 --> 20:15.200
is an important
thing.

20:17.320 --> 20:18.640
I think...

20:21.400 --> 20:22.680
I've lost them.

20:24.440 --> 20:26.800
I've lost my family.

20:26.800 --> 20:28.320
I don't believe that.

20:29.680 --> 20:31.800
You didn't see
their faces.

20:31.800 --> 20:35.720
They looked at me
like I wasn't part of them,

20:35.720 --> 20:39.440
like I wasn't--
like I wasn't one of them.

20:40.680 --> 20:43.440
They looked at me
like a stranger...

20:44.440 --> 20:47.120
not even a stranger.

20:49.200 --> 20:51.400
Like an enemy.

20:55.640 --> 20:58.000
I've lost my family.

20:59.280 --> 21:01.120
[sobs]

21:01.120 --> 21:02.200
Where are you?

21:04.120 --> 21:05.080
Nova?

21:06.240 --> 21:08.080
Home.

21:08.080 --> 21:10.320
Okay, good.

21:13.000 --> 21:15.080
[sobbing]

21:15.080 --> 21:16.280
Just breathe,
sweetheart.

21:16.280 --> 21:17.480
Just breathe.

21:21.520 --> 21:24.320
[woman vocalizing]

21:24.320 --> 21:26.840
[Violet] We are
being tried, Lord...

21:28.200 --> 21:30.480
but I know you got us.

21:30.480 --> 21:33.640
so I thank you.

21:33.640 --> 21:37.600
I thank you for keeping us
in your safe place,

21:37.600 --> 21:43.040
Charley, Micah,
Ralph Angel, Blue.

21:44.280 --> 21:48.480
And I always thank you
for Hollywood.

21:51.920 --> 21:54.520
And I ask you to help me.

21:57.120 --> 22:00.600
I do miss
that stubborn child.

22:01.920 --> 22:04.840
I-- Though I
just can't with her.

22:08.240 --> 22:10.080
So you watch over her.

22:13.080 --> 22:14.280
Bless Nova.

22:16.080 --> 22:18.680
Touch her mind and heart...

22:20.920 --> 22:25.680
so that she knows the hurt
she done caused.

22:29.200 --> 22:30.600
And keep her safe.

22:31.600 --> 22:33.040
Amen.

22:40.000 --> 22:41.680
Lavoisier.

22:41.680 --> 22:43.680
L-A-V-O-I-S-I-E-R.

22:45.080 --> 22:47.200
Yeah. Thanks.

22:47.200 --> 22:48.360
-[hangs up]
-[knock on door]

22:48.360 --> 22:49.600
One sec!

22:54.920 --> 22:55.920
You came.

22:55.920 --> 22:57.120
[chuckles]

22:57.120 --> 22:59.280
I did.

22:59.280 --> 23:00.480
Can I come in?

23:07.080 --> 23:08.880
My visit isn't
about me or us.

23:08.880 --> 23:10.200
It's about you.

23:10.200 --> 23:13.720
Me? Well-- Well,
I'm struggling.

23:13.720 --> 23:15.200
That's me right now.

23:15.200 --> 23:17.240
All right,
let's talk about it.

23:17.240 --> 23:18.920
[knock on door]

23:20.600 --> 23:21.840
-Hey.
-Micah!

23:21.840 --> 23:23.360
-What's up?
-[chuckles]

23:23.360 --> 23:26.120
Just, um,
returning your keys.

23:26.120 --> 23:27.840
-Thanks.
-Yeah.

23:27.840 --> 23:29.120
Glad you're here.

23:29.120 --> 23:31.400
Meet Calvin. This is
my nephew Micah.

23:31.400 --> 23:33.360
I've heard great things
about you, Micah.

23:33.360 --> 23:35.080
You're the cop?

23:36.720 --> 23:38.240
Ex-cop.

23:40.080 --> 23:41.680
You know, I'm thinking
I should make a sign

23:41.680 --> 23:43.360
or something
so everybody knows.

23:46.840 --> 23:48.880
I'm gonna make
a phone call,
if you don't mind.

23:48.880 --> 23:50.400
I'm gonna be
on the back porch.

23:50.400 --> 23:51.160
Of course.

23:54.600 --> 23:55.600
Go on.

23:55.600 --> 23:57.360
Say what's on your mind.

23:57.360 --> 23:59.240
I know
you're disappointed.

23:59.240 --> 24:01.000
Ah, it's none
of my business.

24:01.000 --> 24:03.680
But you're feeling
some type of way about it.

24:03.680 --> 24:04.680
Tell me.

24:04.680 --> 24:06.040
Radical truth.

24:06.040 --> 24:07.720
Have you been with him
the whole time?

24:07.720 --> 24:10.200
No. You read the book.

24:10.200 --> 24:12.840
So did he. We just
recently reunited on tour.

24:12.840 --> 24:15.280
But don't you feel weird
being with a cop?

24:15.280 --> 24:16.680
A white cop?

24:16.680 --> 24:18.280
Like Orson?

24:18.280 --> 24:19.560
He's not that type of cop.

24:19.560 --> 24:20.920
He doesn't abuse people.

24:20.920 --> 24:23.280
What? You know?
You asked him?

24:23.280 --> 24:25.920
No, not directly.

24:25.920 --> 24:28.480
I've known Calvin
a long time.

24:28.480 --> 24:30.240
I know his heart.

24:30.240 --> 24:31.720
He's not
the kind of person

24:31.720 --> 24:33.400
to beat up
black and brown people.

24:33.400 --> 24:36.200
Okay, but he's seen
other cops do it.

24:37.360 --> 24:38.560
I-I don't know.

24:38.560 --> 24:39.920
All right,
so you're okay

24:39.920 --> 24:41.720
being with somebody
who will stand by

24:41.720 --> 24:44.240
and watch other cops
do that kind of abuse,

24:44.240 --> 24:46.640
watch other cops do
what Orson did to me.

24:52.080 --> 24:54.840
-[crowd murmuring]
-What's up, everybody?

24:54.840 --> 24:58.240
-What's up, man?
-Got your checks for the week.

24:58.240 --> 25:01.440
Know there's been
a lot of talk about
what's going on,

25:01.440 --> 25:04.320
so I just want to be
honest with y'all.

25:04.320 --> 25:07.080
You know,
our program under review

25:07.080 --> 25:10.240
'til they figure out
what's happening.

25:10.240 --> 25:13.320
Heard about
what happened with
your sister's mill.

25:13.320 --> 25:15.360
I'm sorry
about that.

25:15.360 --> 25:17.560
But I gotta ask,
man.

25:17.560 --> 25:20.000
We still got jobs
or not?

25:21.040 --> 25:22.360
I been talking
to other farms

25:22.360 --> 25:24.840
-about any open positions.
-Uh-huh, man.

25:24.840 --> 25:26.400
-What about this farm?
-Yeah.

25:26.400 --> 25:28.360
Doing my best
to keep my word.

25:30.680 --> 25:32.440
The Public Safety
and Corrections Board,

25:32.440 --> 25:34.320
man, they pay a part
of y'all's salary.

25:34.320 --> 25:36.800
Until we out of review,

25:36.800 --> 25:39.040
can't keep everybody.

25:39.040 --> 25:42.400
-[workers murmuring]
-This is crazy.

26:10.280 --> 26:14.440
♪ Echoes start
As a cross in you ♪

26:16.240 --> 26:20.360
♪ Trembling noises
That come too soon ♪

26:22.080 --> 26:25.280
♪ Spatial movement
Which seems to you ♪

26:25.280 --> 26:27.400
[pounding]

26:27.400 --> 26:32.040
♪ Resonating
Your mask or feud ♪

26:33.600 --> 26:39.280
♪ Hollow talking
And hollow girl ♪

26:39.280 --> 26:44.040
♪ Force it out
From the root of pain ♪

26:44.040 --> 26:46.400
[camera clicking]

26:46.400 --> 26:48.400
♪ Never said it was good ♪

26:48.400 --> 26:52.720
♪ Never said it was near ♪

26:52.720 --> 26:56.720
♪ Shadow rises
And you are here ♪

27:02.080 --> 27:03.080
[sighs]

27:07.400 --> 27:08.920
♪ And then you cut ♪

27:14.360 --> 27:16.360
♪ You cut it out ♪

27:21.480 --> 27:23.240
♪ And everything ♪

27:29.800 --> 27:33.360
♪ Goes back to the beginning ♪

27:40.560 --> 27:42.200
♪ And then you cut ♪

27:42.200 --> 27:44.200
[sobbing]

27:48.720 --> 27:52.280
♪ Goes back to the beginning ♪

27:53.480 --> 27:55.240
[metal creaks]

27:59.400 --> 28:00.480
[footsteps crunching]

28:00.480 --> 28:02.720
♪ Never said it was good ♪

28:02.720 --> 28:06.880
♪ Never said it was near ♪

28:16.600 --> 28:18.200
[sniffles]

28:23.880 --> 28:26.280
Have you come to gloat?

28:26.280 --> 28:27.600
No, Charley.

28:27.600 --> 28:31.320
From one business owner
to another,

28:31.320 --> 28:33.440
I came
to pay my respects.

28:35.400 --> 28:36.600
Respect.

28:39.840 --> 28:43.680
None of you even know
the meaning of that word.

28:46.280 --> 28:48.840
Especially Frances.

28:48.840 --> 28:51.200
I warned you
about my sister.

28:51.200 --> 28:52.320
Mmm.

28:54.800 --> 28:56.880
Well, I know she
had something to do

28:56.880 --> 28:59.680
with all of this.

29:01.800 --> 29:04.800
And I know
your sorry excuse
for a family

29:04.800 --> 29:06.720
is in business
with Hank Miller

29:06.720 --> 29:09.320
and Old World Energy.

29:10.800 --> 29:12.280
I want you to know...

29:14.280 --> 29:18.800
I would never physically
hurt your or your family,

29:18.800 --> 29:20.080
not like this.

29:20.080 --> 29:23.120
My hands
are clean on this.

29:23.120 --> 29:24.320
I promise you.

29:24.320 --> 29:26.600
Sam, I will
never believe

29:26.600 --> 29:28.600
a word that comes
out of your mouth...

29:29.640 --> 29:31.000
so just go,

29:31.000 --> 29:33.280
and leave me alone.

29:49.520 --> 29:51.520
[R & B playing]

30:05.840 --> 30:09.440
This was actually
very delicious.

30:10.680 --> 30:12.440
You're a good cook.

30:12.440 --> 30:16.040
Least I could do
for all you done...

30:17.440 --> 30:19.640
help with my fam,

30:19.640 --> 30:20.840
my reentry guys,

30:20.840 --> 30:23.760
just being there for me.

30:26.280 --> 30:27.800
I appreciate you.

30:30.760 --> 30:36.320
I know letting
your workers go
today was tough,

30:36.320 --> 30:41.200
but you did what
you had to do for now.

30:42.840 --> 30:47.840
Just keep your head up

30:47.840 --> 30:49.800
and looking forward.

30:49.800 --> 30:51.480
Yeah.

30:52.880 --> 30:56.000
Even if we save
the program,

30:56.000 --> 30:58.680
still the highway coming
to take away the farm.

30:58.680 --> 31:04.000
I feel like I just
keep letting down
my Pops, you know?

31:05.960 --> 31:07.680
[clears throat]

31:07.680 --> 31:09.280
I respect that.

31:11.240 --> 31:13.240
The feelings
are real,

31:13.240 --> 31:18.120
but it don't mean
they're always
the truth.

31:18.120 --> 31:19.800
[chuckles]

31:21.800 --> 31:23.600
Looks like things
always work out for you.

31:23.600 --> 31:25.320
[sighs]

31:25.320 --> 31:26.640
No, I really be wondering

31:26.640 --> 31:30.680
how some people just be
so blessed, you know?

31:31.800 --> 31:32.840
And then others...

31:32.840 --> 31:34.440
[sighs]

31:37.400 --> 31:39.040
they just seem cursed.

31:45.400 --> 31:48.280
I was still
breast-feeding

31:48.280 --> 31:51.280
and studying
for the bar

31:51.280 --> 31:54.840
when Joie's dad
disappeared
for six months.

31:57.320 --> 31:59.200
I thought my life
was over,

31:59.200 --> 32:01.040
almost lost my house.

32:03.600 --> 32:06.840
Had a job offer
that depended

32:06.840 --> 32:12.600
on me passing the bar,
but I was exhausted

32:12.600 --> 32:15.760
from being up
with Joie all night.

32:15.760 --> 32:19.720
But I took it
one day at a time...

32:21.080 --> 32:22.640
and I got
through it.

32:24.000 --> 32:27.200
Small goals
started adding up
to big strides,

32:27.200 --> 32:32.680
and eventually
I found a way
to make it work.

32:34.240 --> 32:39.240
You can either
let fear stall you...

32:40.400 --> 32:42.000
or drive you.

32:46.320 --> 32:48.120
Let it drive you.

32:49.280 --> 32:52.520
♪ Don't, woman ♪

32:53.840 --> 32:56.480
♪ Treat him wrong ♪

33:02.240 --> 33:04.440
♪ As the saying goes ♪

33:06.200 --> 33:09.400
♪ A good man
is hard to find... ♪

33:09.400 --> 33:10.600
Stay with me tonight?

33:13.400 --> 33:17.680
♪ A good man
is so hard to find ♪

33:20.200 --> 33:23.280
♪ If you want ♪

33:24.440 --> 33:28.080
♪ The one you love... ♪

33:29.480 --> 33:32.320
I missed you so much.

33:32.320 --> 33:33.560
I missed you, too.

33:38.640 --> 33:41.520
Micah,
I just wanted to say...

33:42.640 --> 33:45.000
-yesterday was--
-Yeah, I know.

33:45.000 --> 33:46.600
All I could think about was,

33:46.600 --> 33:48.600
what if you and your mom
had been in there?

33:48.600 --> 33:49.760
I know.
Thankfully we weren't.

33:49.760 --> 33:51.840
I know,
but what if you had?

33:51.840 --> 33:53.320
I don't know
what I would have done.

33:53.320 --> 33:54.520
It's all good, baby.

33:54.520 --> 33:56.640
Just wait.
Stop interrupting me.

33:58.400 --> 34:01.760
I'm trying
to tell you something.

34:01.760 --> 34:03.680
[sighs]

34:03.680 --> 34:05.840
I love you, too.

34:05.840 --> 34:07.080
[chuckles]

34:07.080 --> 34:09.120
[chuckles]

34:12.120 --> 34:14.120
[distant train horn blowing]

34:19.520 --> 34:21.840
I don't know if it's
the right time or not,

34:21.840 --> 34:25.520
but prom is coming up.

34:25.520 --> 34:27.640
Yeah, it is pretty soon, huh?

34:27.640 --> 34:30.600
Yeah, so I--

34:30.600 --> 34:35.760
I think we should talk
about making plans
for prom.

34:35.760 --> 34:37.320
Now?

34:39.320 --> 34:40.440
Okay.

34:41.680 --> 34:44.240
Uh, I'm gonna get a tux,

34:44.240 --> 34:47.840
you know,
get a limousine.

34:47.840 --> 34:49.640
You could pick
the colors if you want.

34:49.640 --> 34:50.640
No, I mean...

34:50.640 --> 34:55.800
I think
we should talk about

34:55.800 --> 35:00.040
making plans
for prom...

35:01.240 --> 35:02.480
night.

35:03.880 --> 35:05.680
Ah. [chuckles]

35:07.800 --> 35:09.080
Plans.

35:11.480 --> 35:12.480
Yeah.

35:14.000 --> 35:15.600
Are you ready?

35:18.000 --> 35:19.640
I'm ready
to talk about it.

35:29.040 --> 35:31.880
[sighs]

35:31.880 --> 35:32.880
That was real good.

35:34.720 --> 35:37.600
Think your greens
got even better,
if it's possible.

35:40.400 --> 35:43.040
I've-- I've never asked.

35:43.040 --> 35:45.400
I've never felt
I needed to ask,

35:45.400 --> 35:48.400
but, after talking
with Micah...

35:48.400 --> 35:49.720
Ask me.

35:49.720 --> 35:51.400
Have you ever used
excessive force?

35:51.400 --> 35:53.280
No.

35:53.280 --> 35:57.040
Have you ever
seen another officer
use excessive force?

35:57.040 --> 35:59.640
Abuse black people?

36:01.440 --> 36:02.640
Yes.

36:03.720 --> 36:05.760
And did you look away?

36:07.600 --> 36:08.680
Yes.

36:13.200 --> 36:15.760
Horrible things
happen.

36:18.040 --> 36:20.440
And you have
to be brave to stand
against the tide,

36:20.440 --> 36:22.600
and I wasn't.
I wasn't brave. I was...

36:26.680 --> 36:28.240
I was a coward.

36:30.800 --> 36:32.440
I'm not trying
to humanize myself

36:32.440 --> 36:34.440
or explain it away.
I'm telling you the truth,

36:34.440 --> 36:39.200
because I want you
to know how it felt
to be inside.

36:39.200 --> 36:41.840
How does
running away help?

36:41.840 --> 36:45.440
Because I
wanted to live
with myself,

36:45.440 --> 36:47.520
not stay
in a toxic
environment,

36:47.520 --> 36:52.200
one that ruined
the most important
relationship in my life.

36:54.480 --> 36:56.720
I didn't want to be
the person you
turned away from.

36:56.720 --> 36:58.600
I wanted to--

36:58.600 --> 36:59.760
to change.

37:01.480 --> 37:02.520
I'm sorry.

37:04.680 --> 37:06.320
And I know
it's not enough.

37:07.880 --> 37:11.160
Your past is
always gonna be there,

37:11.160 --> 37:13.680
always gonna be
a new challenge.

37:13.680 --> 37:16.880
Because of it,
there's no way
to erase it.

37:16.880 --> 37:18.320
Why would I
want to do that?

37:21.000 --> 37:24.520
My past led me to you,

37:24.520 --> 37:27.840
and that led me
to want to be
a better man.

37:48.800 --> 37:50.800
[cell phone buzzing]

38:06.200 --> 38:08.040
Hello.

38:08.040 --> 38:09.240
Ralph Angel?

38:12.000 --> 38:13.280
Darla.

38:13.280 --> 38:15.320
I called you
to see how things are.

38:15.320 --> 38:16.840
Still here.

38:16.840 --> 38:18.920
About all I got.

38:18.920 --> 38:20.840
I know what that
feels like.

38:23.200 --> 38:24.880
It sucks.

38:25.960 --> 38:27.440
How's Blue?

38:28.440 --> 38:30.600
Fine. [chuckles]

38:30.600 --> 38:33.400
He started his little
Blue corner thing early

38:33.400 --> 38:34.920
over
at Aunt Vi's tonight.

38:34.920 --> 38:37.960
I can, um-- I can come by
and pick him up

38:37.960 --> 38:40.800
and take the weight
off of you for a while
if you want.

38:42.000 --> 38:43.320
No, you good.

38:44.400 --> 38:46.520
Talked to him
earlier.

38:46.520 --> 38:48.160
Been asleep,

38:48.160 --> 38:50.200
not before he
told me he didn't
want to be

38:50.200 --> 38:52.880
a marine biologist
no more. Heh.

38:52.880 --> 38:54.280
Talking about,
uh...

38:54.280 --> 38:56.280
[both]
Going to space.

38:56.280 --> 38:57.880
Yeah.

38:57.880 --> 38:59.480
I don't know.

38:59.480 --> 39:02.080
I feel like he
growing up right
in front of us.

39:02.080 --> 39:05.160
Isn't he amazing?

39:05.160 --> 39:06.880
Yeah.
He's figuring
it out,

39:06.880 --> 39:09.840
just like
all of us.

39:10.840 --> 39:12.200
[liquid pouring]

39:12.200 --> 39:14.440
♪ I'm not gonna
Take the blame ♪

39:14.440 --> 39:16.960
♪ 'Cause you
Keep on running ♪

39:18.160 --> 39:19.840
♪ Keep on running ♪

39:21.160 --> 39:25.880
♪ Away from me ♪

39:25.880 --> 39:27.960
♪ I'm not gonna
Play this game ♪

39:27.960 --> 39:30.440
♪ Where I keep on beggin' ♪

39:31.840 --> 39:33.840
♪ Keep on askin' ♪

39:34.840 --> 39:37.880
♪ What you need ♪

39:37.880 --> 39:38.880
Is this true?

39:48.040 --> 39:51.000
Migrant workers
that were killed
during the hurricane

39:51.000 --> 39:53.600
when their boss
told them to keep working,
that was you?

39:54.880 --> 39:56.480
Why didn't you tell me?

39:58.200 --> 40:00.040
I don't know.

40:00.040 --> 40:02.000
I was embarrassed.

40:02.000 --> 40:03.840
You were embarrassed
because you were guilty.

40:05.000 --> 40:06.960
You forced people to work
in a hurricane.

40:06.960 --> 40:08.840
You cost two men
their lives.

40:08.840 --> 40:11.520
I tried to fix it,

40:11.520 --> 40:13.520
for all
the difference
it made.

40:13.520 --> 40:16.000
Wh-What does that mean?

40:16.000 --> 40:20.080
I wish I could change
what happened then...

40:21.680 --> 40:22.840
but I can't.

40:24.800 --> 40:27.400
I wish I could change
what's happening now, but...

40:28.880 --> 40:30.600
Th-That's your answer?

40:31.920 --> 40:35.200
You lost your building,
your business,

40:35.200 --> 40:36.480
and that's terrible,

40:36.480 --> 40:38.840
but these men
lost their lives.

40:41.800 --> 40:43.240
Is this
the real you?

40:49.160 --> 40:50.200
Yeah.

40:53.640 --> 40:55.080
Yeah, I guess it is.

41:00.480 --> 41:05.320
♪ I don't wanna make
An empty promise ♪

41:06.440 --> 41:08.640
♪ I ain't got time ♪

41:09.800 --> 41:13.280
♪ To tell you lies ♪

41:13.280 --> 41:19.000
♪ No, I ain't gonna pull you
Through the darkness ♪

41:20.040 --> 41:22.960
♪ But I can show you ♪

41:22.960 --> 41:28.160
♪ Where to find a light ♪

41:28.160 --> 41:30.200
[song continues]

41:34.920 --> 41:40.600
♪ Ooh, ooh, yeah ♪

41:40.600 --> 41:47.000
♪ No, I ain't gonna pull you
Through the darkness ♪

41:47.000 --> 41:49.400
♪ But I can show you ♪

41:50.480 --> 41:53.280
♪ Where to find a light ♪

42:02.000 --> 42:03.440
[woman]
Go, Ree-Ree.
